<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. sigmoides" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" rank="species" species="sigmoides">D. sigmoides</taxonomicName>
, differing from the latter by three bristles on notopleura, five transverse hair combs on hind metatarsus, 21 dorsal costal cilia, and a larger size. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Dahliphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dahliphora zaitzevi" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">Dahliphora zaitzevi</taxonomicName>
is the only species of the genus which is distributed in the temperate area.
</paragraph>
